     <div type="to_the_reader">
   <pb facs="2"/>
   <head>To the Christian Reader.</head>
   <p>
      <note n="a" place="bottom">Eph. 5.14.</note>
      <hi>AWake and
<note n="b" place="bottom">Cant. 2.10.</note> Arise,
<note n="c" place="bottom">Iohn 1.46.</note> Come and see,
<note n="*" place="bottom">
            <hi>August. lib.</hi> 8. <hi>confess. cap.</hi> 12.</note> Take vp and reade,
<note n="d" place="bottom">Luke 8.50.</note> BEleeue and
<note n="e" place="bottom">Ioh. 15.20.</note> remember,
<note n="f" place="bottom">Psal. 34.14.</note> Doe good, and
<note n="g" place="bottom">Phil. 1.29.</note> suffer,
<note n="h" place="bottom">Luk. 22.32.</note> Strengthen others and
<note n="i" place="bottom">Psal. 147.12.</note> praise God.</hi>
   </p>
   <q>
      <bibl>
         <hi>EPHES. 6. vers. 18.</hi>
      </bibl>
      <p>And pray alwaies with all manner of prayer and sup<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>plication in the spirit, and watch thereunto with all perseuerance.</p>
      <bibl>
         <hi>1. THES. 5.23, 24, 25.</hi>
      </bibl>
      <p>Now the very God of peace sanctifie you throughout, and I pray God that your whole spirit, and soule, and bodie may be kept blamelesse vnto the com<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ming of our Lord Iesus Christ.</p>
      <p>Faithfull is hee which calleth you, who also will doe it.</p>
      <p>Brethren pray for vs.</p>
   </q>
